 Federal House of Representatives PHOTO: Twitter  Its ad hoc committee that is investigating the Appropriation Acts of and capital projects executed by ministries, departments, and agencies (MDAs), noted that there had been “multi-million naira contract repetition by the commission over the years.” While declaring the panel’s public hearing open in Abuja, the House Speaker, Femi Gbajabiamila, decried the low turnout of government agencies. Represented by the House Leader, Alhassan Ado Doguwa, the Speaker vowed that the Abubakar Makki Yalleman-led committee would not be deterred from diligently carrying out its duties. [AD] To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .